---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Government Policies | Policy"
  description="Understand the government policies that shape and influence the UK Armed Forces Compensation Scheme. Learn about current initiatives and future directions in veteran support.">
  <div class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">Government Policies Affecting AFCS</h1>
    <div class="row g-4">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <p class="lead">The Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS) is influenced by various government policies aimed at supporting veterans and service personnel. This page outlines key policies and initiatives that shape the AFCS and veteran support in the UK.</p>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">The Armed Forces Covenant</h2>
        <p>A key policy framework affecting veteran support:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Ensures fair treatment for the Armed Forces community</li>
          <li>Influences local and national decision-making on veteran issues</li>
          <li>Promotes support in areas such as healthcare, housing, and education</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Veterans' Strategy</h2>
        <p>The UK government's long-term plan for veteran support:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Outlines key areas of focus for veteran welfare</li>
          <li>Sets goals for improving support services</li>
          <li>Influences funding and resource allocation for veteran programmes</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Defence People Mental Health and Wellbeing Strategy</h2>
        <p>Addressing mental health needs of service personnel and veterans:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Promotes early intervention and prevention</li>
          <li>Aims to reduce stigma around mental health in the Armed Forces</li>
          <li>Influences AFCS policies on mental health compensation</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Transition Policy</h2>
        <p>Supporting service leavers in their transition to civilian life:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provides guidance on career transition services</li>
          <li>Influences AFCS support for education and training</li>
          <li>Aims to ensure smooth integration into civilian society</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Continuous Improvement Policy</h2>
        <p>Ongoing efforts to enhance the AFCS:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Regular reviews of compensation levels and eligibility criteria</li>
          <li>Incorporation of feedback from veterans and stakeholders</li>
          <li>Adaptation to changing needs of the veteran community</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Cross-Government Collaboration</h2>
        <p>Efforts to ensure coordinated support for veterans:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Collaboration between Ministry of Defence, NHS, and other departments</li>
          <li>Development of integrated support pathways</li>
          <li>Sharing of data and best practices across government bodies</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Related Information</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
              <li><a href="/policy/legislation" class="text-decoration-none">AFCS Legislation</a></li>
              <li><a href="/policy/recent-changes" class="text-decoration-none">Recent Policy Changes</a></li>
              <li><a href="/support/veteran-support-services" class="text-decoration-none">Veteran Support Services</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Policy Consultation</h3>
            <p>Participate in ongoing consultations on veteran support policies.</p>
            <a href="/policy-consultation" class="btn btn-primary">Have Your Say</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
